gov.usgs.anss.edgeoutput

Class DeleteBlockInfo

  • java.lang.Object
    • gov.usgs.anss.edgeoutput.DeleteBlockInfo
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable

    public class DeleteBlockInfo
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable
    This information is about the location of a single block. The instance # and julian get a file name, the indexBlock, extent, and block with he indexBlock itself give an individual block. These objects are exchanged when the delete() or replace() features of the CWBEditor are exchanged from the QueryServer.

               short latest)
        Make a new DBI with the various elements
        Parameters:
        seedname - NNSSSSSCCCLL seedname format
        instance - An up to 4 character instance name of a CWB which created the data
        julian - The julian day this DBI is on.
        indexBlock - the index block in the IndexFile whose filename comes from julian and instance.
        extent - The extent index number of the proper extent in the index block
        block - The block offset from the extent start of this block
        earliest - The time of day in seconds divided by 3 of the earliest time in the extent
        latest - The time of day in seconds divided by 3 which encloses the latest time in the extent
